comment.text: This translation key is used to display a message encouraging users to complete a form again. It is linked to a button in a completed form UI element.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation "تعبئة مرة أخرى" while literally meaning 'filling out again', doesn't quite capture the nuance of 'Fill it out again'. It sounds more like an instruction to fill out a form that already exists, rather than a request to redo it. A more accurate translation, emphasizing the redo aspect, might be something like 'املأها مرة أخرى' (imla'ha marra ukhra) or 'أعد تعبئتها' (a'id ta'bi'ataha).
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: أعد تعبئتها (a'id ta'bi'ataha) or املأها مرة أخرى (imla'ha marra ukhra)

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation "Συμπλήρωση ξανά" is a literal translation of 'Fill it out again' but doesn't quite capture the natural flow of the instruction in Greek. It implies filling *something* out again, rather than a form specifically.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: A more natural translation would be something like "Γέμισε το ξανά" or "Συμπλήρωσε το ξανά" depending on the context. 'Γέμισε' emphasizes filling, while 'Συμπλήρωσε' is a general term for completing something.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: While "Vuelva a rellenarlo" is understandable, a more natural and common Spanish translation for "Fill it out again" would be "Por favor, rellénalo de nuevo" or "Rellénalo otra vez". "Vuelva a rellenarlo" sounds a bit formal and less conversational.

The translation "ຕື່ມມັນໃ່ໝູ່ຄັ້ງອີກ" is not the most natural or accurate translation of "Fill it out again." While "ຕື່ມ" (teum) means 'fill,' "ມັນໃ່ໝູ່ຄັ້ງອີກ" (man lai muu khang eek) is awkward phrasing. A more common and natural phrasing would be something like "ຕື່ມໃ່ໝູ່ອີກຄັ້ງ" (teum lai muu eek khang) or "ຕື່ມໃ່ໝູ່ຄືນອີກ" (teum lai muu khuen eek).
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: ຕື່ມໃ່ໝູ່ອີກຄັ້ງ

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'නැවත එය පුරවන්න' while understandable, isn't the most natural or idiomatic way to say 'Fill it out again' in Sinhala. A more common and direct translation would be 'ඊයේ නැවත පුරවන්න' (Eeye navetha puravanna) or 'ඊයේ නැවත කරන්න' (Eeye navetha karanna).
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: ඊයේ නැවත පුරවන්න (Eeye navetha puravanna) or ඊයේ නැවත කරන්න (Eeye navetha karanna)

ai_spell_check_issues.description: While 'Vyplňte ho znova' is understandable, a more natural and precise translation of "Fill it out again" would be 'Prosím, vyplňte to ešte raz' or 'Vyplňte to znova, prosím'. 'Ho' is grammatically awkward here as 'it' can refer to multiple things.

While "Попуни поново" is understandable, it's not the most natural or idiomatic translation of "Fill it out again." It literally translates to "Fill it up again." A more common and appropriate translation would be something like "Исправи га поново" or "Напуни га поново", or even just "Напуни поново".

While "Popuni ponovo" is understandable, a more natural and idiomatic Serbian translation of "Fill it out again" would be "Ispunite ga ponovo." "Popuni" implies filling something with material, not completing a form.

While "Điền lại thông tin" is understandable, a more natural and accurate translation of "Fill it out again" would be "Xin điền lại" or "Vui lòng điền lại". "Điền lại thông tin" literally translates to 'Fill the information again' which is not as concise and fluent.
